<h2>Installation</h2>
<p>To install Fountain Music, just launch the installer (&ldquo;Install Fountain Music&rdquo;) and click install.  Once installation is complete, you will need to restart iTunes to start using Fountain Music.</p>

<h2>Use</h2>
<p>To activate Fountain Music, simply select it in the View &gt; Visualizer menu and activate the visualizer with &ldquo;Show Visualizer&rdquo; in the View menu.  You can enter or exit full screen mode by pressing  &#x2318;-F.</p>

<p>Once Fountain Music has been launched, you can display the current track info by pressing the letter &lsquo;i&rsquo;. The &lsquo;[ ]&rsquo; and &lsquo;\&rsquo; keys are used to control the fountain patterns.  Pressing &lsquo;[&lsquo; and &lsquo;]&rsquo; selects the previous and next patterns, respectively. Pressing &lsquo;\&rsquo; stops the pattern from switching on its own.</p>

<p>Just below the pattern controls, the &lsquo;;&rsquo; (semicolon) and &lsquo;&#x27;&rsquo; (single quote) keys change the color scheme, switching to the next and previous color schemes, respectively.
By pressing the &lsquo;&lt;&lsquo; and &lsquo;&gt;&rsquo; keys, you can make the particles have fuzzier or sharper edges, respectively.  The &lsquo;~&rsquo; key will display the advanced menu, which tells of the keys to press to see the frame rate (&lsquo;f&rsquo; key) or number of particles (&lsquo;p&rsquo; key).</p>

<p>The &lsquo;+&rsquo; and &lsquo;-&rsquo; keys make the particles bigger and smaller, respectively. &lsquo;v&rsquo; shows the current version.  If you forget any of these controls, there is a menu available by pressing &lsquo;h&rsquo;, &lsquo;?&rsquo;, or &lsquo;~&rsquo;.</p>

<p>To summarize, the key commands are:</p>
