<p>Finally, the settings dialog is accessible via the &ldquo;Options&hellip;&rdquo; menu item at the end of the View &gt; Visualizer menu.  The &ldquo;Default&rdquo; button will return all preferences to their original values.  &ldquo;OK&rdquo; closes the dialog window and keeps all changes you have made. &ldquo;Cancel&rdquo; also closes the window, but does not save your changes.</p>

<h2>About the Color Schemes</h2>
<p>Beginning with version 2.0, there are a variety of color schemes included with Fountain Music.  These schemes determine what colors particles will be.  Some color schemes change subtly over time, so if you wait for a few seconds the fountain may have an entirely different feel to it. In more detail, the color schemes are:</p>

<ul>
<li><span class='title'>Classic</span>: the original Fountain Music color scheme.  The fountain progresses slowly through the color wheel.</li>
<li><span class='title'>Red, White and Blue</span>: you know that these three colors are the main colors of the flags of Chile, France, Liberia, Malaysia, The Netherlands, Nepal, North Korea, Norway, Iceland, Panama, Puerto Rico, Taiwan, Luxembourg and the UK? <span class='footnote'>(CIA World Factbook)</span>  Hmm, wait a second, that list seems a bit short, I definitely forgot a few minor places.  Oh well, email me if you figure it out..</li>
<li><span class='title'>Fire</span>: Your music bursts into flames with this color scheme!  Okay, not literally, that would be bad, but it does look nice and warm.  Large particles with fuzzy edges are recommended for the full firey effect.</li>
<li><span class='title'>Random</span>: Particles appear in whatever color they feel like. Reminds me of a birthday party, or clowns, or rainbow sprinkles.  Mmmm, rainbow sprinkles.</li>
<li><span class='title'>Sea</span>: A blue-greenish color scheme.  The fountain looks vaguely like elegantly flowing water from the deep sea&hellip; after it has been thrown into a blender with some seaweed and blue food coloring.</li>
<li><span class='title'>Snow</span>: A pure white color scheme. Make snow with your music!</li>
</ul>

